The paper deals with objective evaluation measures of explanations of complex black-box machine learning models, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and specifically machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the fidelity and sensitivity of explanations, which are concepts that are relevant to the field of computational ethics (cs.CE) and security and privacy (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes modifications to improve the fidelity and sensitivity of explanations, which could be relevant to the field of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
